
'''MyWare = a new brand of applications that gather personal data of a user (such as the music playing history) and use it to repurpose, augment and collectively data-mine it'''

"Felix Miller from last.fm introduced the term “Myware�? to the audience, a new brand of applications that gather personal data of a user (such as the music playing history) and use it to repurpose, augment and collectively data-mine it. The realization which last.fm has come to is that users are eager to collect and share this data if there are immediate benefits. In the case of last.fm, users receive a wealth of personalized recommendation from the universe of other users, they can connect to others around the world and build new communities without any extra effort – all the data comes from using their media player, as they always do. Furthermore, the data is not locked-up in any way, as last.fm exposes literally all of it through RSS and web services. This is an example of a promising new direction, by which businesses provide open data aggregation services in return for user benefits and supplementary monetization – a balance of privacy, responsibility and fairness that users would be willing to accept and that may serve companies like last.fm well."
(http://www.openbusiness.cc/2006/03/08/e-tech-day-1-lastfm-defines-open-myware/)

